  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place the <strong>coconut cream sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot, with a matching lid, with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> basmati</strong>&nbsp;<strong>rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>cold water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>eggs</strong> to a separate pot of <strong>salted boiled water</strong> over a high heat (salt prevents the eggs from cracking)</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, boil for exactly 7 min, for perfect, mid-boiled eggs</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, fill a bowl of very cold water with ice (Gousto's ice packs are perfect) ready for cooling your eggs quickly later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile<strong>,</strong>&nbsp;heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> onion</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min or until slightly softened</p>\r\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>sweet potato</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>turmeric</strong> and cook for 5 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/489.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
